text: Gura sort of mentioned it,but it wasn‚Äôt super clear. As most should know,Whales,Porpoises and Dolphins are not sharks,nor are they fish! They are actually Mammals. They are in a family named Cetacea and they are actually considered Hoofed Mammals or Ungulates. This is based on genetic and anatomical evidence. Cetaceans are part of the Even Toed Ungulates or Artiodactyls,a family that include Pigs,Sheep,Cows,Deer,Antelope,Giraffes and many other animals.  The closest living relatives to the Cetaceans are actually the two living species of Hippos (The Common and Pygmy Hippos),which is somewhat ironic and fitting considering both groups of animals both evolved aquatic lifestyles,though to different extents
